description:
Welcome to the YouTube Channel of the Robotics and Perception Group led by Prof. Davide Scaramuzza. Our lab was founded in February 2012 and is part of the Department of Informatics at the University of Zurich, and the Department of Neuroinformatics, of the University of Zurich and ETH Zurich.

Our mission is to develop autonomous machines that can navigate all by themselves using only onboard cameras, without relying on external infrastructure, such as GPS or motion capture systems. Our interests encompass both ground and micro flying robots, as well as multi-robot heterogeneous systems consisting of the combination of these two. We do not want our machines to be passive, but active, in that they should react to and navigate within their environment so as to gain the best knowledge from it.

description:
Hi all!!!

My name is Jim and I'm the creator of this channel. This is my full time job and my mission is to bring you the highest quality and of high standard editing BeamNG drive videos with unique, meaningful and fun content.

BeamNG drive is the most realistic driving game that mimics every component of a vehicle in real time resulting in lifelike behavior.

All my videos are created by myself using the following programs : GeForce Experience for recording, Adobe Premiere Pro for editing and synchronizing the initially raw footage and Photoshop for thumbnails.

My weekly process consists of:
- Recording my clips ( 30 - 40 hours )
- Editing my clips ( 18 - 24 hours ) That includes editing in image, music, captions and sound effects.
-Thumbnails, description etc. roughly 10 hours.

I upload 3 times a week every Tuesday, Friday and Sunday, at 5pm GMT

Join me and be part of this adventure. 

Subscribe and stay tuned!

Hello, I'm Andy. My goal is to create entertaining videos mostly, but not only, for people who love cars & crashes. 

All the videos you'll find in this channel are recorded & edited by me and my sidekick, George, who helps with parts of the editing.
This channel is our full-time job. We're devoting a minimum of 100 hours per week to bring you the best BeamNG drive videos.

How we work:

Creating these videos is a lot harder & time consuming than you might think but it is what makes us and, hopefully, you happy!
We are playing BeamNG.drive, a PC Game featuring the ultimate soft-body physics and realism. 

The process, step by step:

- Recording the clips with Action! (10-15 hours, sometimes 15+)
- Editing & synchronizing the clips with music & addition of captions / sound effects - Premiere Pro (5-10 hours)  
- Descriptions, Thumbnails etc.  (2 hours)

We’re uploading 4 Videos per week on Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday & Sunday. Stay up to date by Subscribing!
Thank you :)

description:
Hello and welcome to my channel.  In 2014 I was asked by my mom to help find something to help her sleep.  She was looking for one of those little boxes you put next to the bed to play nature sounds, and asked me to help.  From what I found, they were terrible.  I realized that I could do so much better for her.  I bought my first recorder and got to work, and she loved them.  

I started my channel in 2015 and it didn't take long to realize that I was going to need a lot more that just a recorder.  And so it began!  Several new computers, nicer recorders, new video camera, and a slew of microphones later, here we are.  You wouldn't believe how much is actually involved with making each video! Every video takes several hours to edit, and that doesn't include the time and travel to actually make the recordings. Totally worth it!

I feel lucky to have helped so many people over the years.  Every recording is unique and I hope to make that perfect video and sound that helps you too.

🏎️ Here you can watch and listen to more than 2000 videos about modern and historic race cars, the pure sound of old F1s but also some raw action from rally, hillclimb or drifting events all edited without music or anyone talking. Just cars and their natural sounds, recorded with high-quality microphones. And I've recently been adding something for two-wheel lovers too! 🏍️

🎧For an even greater sense of immersion, you can also find videos recorded using binaural microphones, labelled as ''[3D Binaural Audio]'' in the title

📸 I couldn't help but fall in love with photography too, sooner or later. You can find my works on Flickr and on my Instagram account @ste19bozzy92

☝️What else? Oh there's my second channel with videos dedicated to airplanes ✈️

description:
Hi! I'm Rachel, here's a little about me.
On April 16, I was in a horrific car wreck that changed my life.
I sustained multiple finger amputations, broken bones, spinal damage, and now live with ongoing chronic pain.
Since then I have had multiple surgeries, lived in a condemned home, fought depression, PTSD, and anxiety, had no than $3 in change to my name, and lived through some of the most life-changing scenarios a person can experience.

Since the day of my wreck I have learned to survive when I thought I couldn't, laughed when life tried to bring me down, love the damaged but beautiful body i have, and know that in every dark tunnel, there will always be enough light to guide you on your path.

description:
The official BUGATTI YouTube Channel

Since its foundation in 1909 by Ettore Bugatti, the brand has been at the pinnacle of the automotive industry, creating the world’s most powerful and luxurious automobiles from its home in Molsheim, France. In the 1920s, BUGATTI became known for its racing successes as well as in the 1930s for Jean Bugatti’s elegant touring cars. In 1991, the EB110 premiered and set new benchmarks for sports car performance. 

With the introduction of the VEYRON 16.4 in 2005, BUGATTI created an entirely new segment: the hyper sports car, becoming the first production model to break through 1,000 PS and 400 km/h. In 2016, the CHIRON once again redefined speed and usability, culminating in a 1,600 PS version breaking the 300mph barrier. 

Today, BUGATTI is part of the BUGATTI Rimac Group and well underway with the development of the next-generation of BUGATTI hyper sports cars, true to Ettore’s motto "If comparable, it is no longer BUGATTI."

Welcome to the official POLAR Mohr YouTube Channel.

POLAR was founded in 1906 as "Adolf Mohr, Maschinenfabrik". Since then, the company has undergone a transformation, not only in terms of the products it focuses on. It has grown from a regional provider to the world’s number one for high-speed cutters and associated peripheral equipment for the graphics industry.
POLAR develops efficient solutions for the post-print sector and is a future-oriented technology company with a global presence. The product range includes components and systems that link up and automate all processes, from loading, jogging, cutting and die-cutting through to unloading and banding.

Subscribe now to not miss any new video!

Music! Dancing! Learning! Bears! 🤸🏻‍♂️🐻👨🏻‍🔬💃

“Danny Go!” is a live-action educational children’s show filled with music, movement and silliness. Created in 2019 by 3 childhood friends in Charlotte, North Carolina, the show inspires learning and off-the-couch exercise for kids ages 3 to 7. 

Here’s what you’ll find in our videos: 
 +  Catchy, upbeat dance-along songs that kids AND parents can enjoy together
 +  Kindergarten-level learning (math basics, vocabulary, science experiments)
 +  Basic lessons about friendship, kindness & respect
 +  Good-natured silliness and fun
 +  Real-life exploration (i.e. animal shelter, fire station, trampoline park)

description:
Hi!
Welcome to Beamng Madness. On this channel, you will see weekly uploaded videos. If you like fast cars and crashing, please consider subscribing :)

How I make the videos:

Making the videos is a lot harder and time-consuming than most people imagine. In fact, each video takes up to five days to complete. Here's a step by step process of the video production: 

1. Creating/setting up one or more maps for the video (5-15 hours)
2. Recording the video (5-8  hours)
3. Editing the video (5-7 hours)
4. Uploading, making the thumbnail, etc. (1-3 hours) 

I rarely have time to relax in the weekends because I'm too busy making a new video for you guys, but when I see your positive feedback it's totally worth it! :)

description:
Welcome, Petrol Heads!! 

TopSpeedGermany is a German Youtube channel for people who love cars.
My Name is Max and I film while driving cars. No matter if they are old, fast, loud or electric. They need to be special! 
With several onboard cams, I record everything important to show you High-Speed-Runs, Acceleration tests 
( 0-100 kph / 0-200 kph  / 100-200 kph / 200-300 kph ) and test drives on German Autobahn or Road.  
Please note, Germany is the country of "no speed limit" highways. So in some places, it's allowed to drive very fast. 
But please don't try this if you are not an experienced driver !!  If you enjoy give a like and subscribe for more videos ;-)

description:
🚄 Welcome to the Official HS2 Channel 🏗️

HS2 is Britain’s new high-speed rail network, designed to transform travel and connect the country like never before. Once operational, HS2’s British-built, zero-carbon bullet trains will slash journey times between London, Birmingham, Manchester, and beyond, integrating with the existing network to reach Scotland and the North West.

But HS2 is more than just a railway—it’s a catalyst for growth. By linking the UK’s biggest economic hubs, it’s driving inner-city regeneration, job creation, and investment. Over 31,000 people are already working on HS2, with 3,200+ UK businesses playing a role in its construction.

🏗️ Building Britain’s Future:
✔️ 140 miles of track
✔️ 54 trains
✔️ 4 state-of-the-art stations
✔️ 32 miles of tunnels & 130 bridges
✔️ 2 maintenance depots

📢 Subscribe for the latest news and updates from Britain’s high-speed railway, HS2.

#HS2 #Train #Rail #Infrastructure #Construction #HighSpeedRail #Engineering

description:
Our mission is to investigate the design of embedded technology for cyber-physical systems.

We perform applied research on the embedded software, hardware and communication technology as applied in cyber-physical systems (CPS). These computational components play a crucial role in the monitoring and control of a CPS. In addition, CoSys-Lab focuses on the development processes of these components.

Our main application domains are: mechatronics, automotive and health & care.

Some typical research examples are: an ultrasound sensor array for localisation, the automotive power window, supportive tooling for AUTOSAR, an autonomously driving wheel chair, etc.

Our research splits up in two main domains: Model-based systems engineering for CPS and Sensors, signal processing and control for CPS.

Yusuf Ansari is a senior journalist, writer, and political Analyst with more than 25 years of experience in print, TV, and digital media. He is currently a freelancer. He writes for various newspapers, such as Navbharat Times, Amar Ujala, Dainik Jagran, and Naya Bharat, and for Digital News Platforms like Satyahindi, New18Hindi, The Quint Hindi, and BBC Hindi.

He started his career in journalism during his college time as a hobby. Later, he obtained a PG Diploma in Hindi Journalism from IIMC, Delhi. He joined ‘Dainik Navjyoti’ as a correspondent. After working for 2.5 years, he joined Zee News as a correspondent and rose to Assistant Editor. He also worked for Sun Star as a political Editor and ‘Sandesh’ as an Input Coordinator.

Welcome to the Advance Driving School YouTube channel! 

We are an independent driving school based in the UK. The videos on our channel suggest ways you can improve your driving, but they are not intended to replace proper driving lessons with an instructor.  Our videos are written to help UK learner drivers perfect the essential driving skills needed to become a safe driver and pass the UK Driving Test. If you are a more experienced driver, or if you live in a different country you may drive in a slightly different way, but we hope you still find our videos interesting.  

Feel free to leave any comments you have about our videos, and if you have a suggestion for the next video we should make please let us know. Please subscribe to our channel, and like your favourite videos as it really helps other people find us.
